modules.description: Provides functions to construct and send HTTP requests, parse JSON responses, and handle error cases during API interactions. Works with request configurations, JSON values, and HTTP client backends. Used to integrate OCaml applications with external web services, such as fetching user data from an API or submitting form inputs.

Provides monadic operations for handling asynchronous HTTP requests and results, including binding, mapping, and error propagation. Works with HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE, returning results as strings or errors. Executes network calls with custom headers and processes responses in a structured, error-aware manner.
